gs through human reaction time experiments, drawing on cognitive science paradigms: if models mimic human implicit bias patterns (e.g., faster rejection of negative sentences with stereotypically 'foreign' names), this strengthens ecological validity. The framework will be applied across multilingual LMs (XLM-R, BLOOM) and evaluated on sentiment, toxicity, and formality tasks. Impact includes a new class of process-based interpretability tools, identification of 'bias emergence points' in architectures, and training strategies that intervene at specific network depths (e.g., freezing late layers during debiasing).",
